Class global

  • java.lang.Object
    • mil.emp3.api.global

  • public class global
extends java.lang.Object
    This static class provides global method to retrieve data or configuration setting. A Note on Input Validation of double values: According to The Java Language Specification (JLS), ยง4.2.3, "Floating-Point Types, Formats, and Values" [JLS 2015]: NaN (not-a-number) is unordered, so the numerical comparison operators <, <=, >, and >= return false if either or both operands are NaN. The equality operator == returns false if either operand is NaN, and the inequality operator != returns true if either operand is NaN.
